Roger Gurnani: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 9:16 PM ET
IT Services

Company Overview of Verizon Nederland B.V.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Roger   Gurnani  Chief Information & Technology Architect and Executive Vice President, Verizon Nederland B.V.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 3 different industries.56--
Background

		Mr. Roger Gurnani served as the Chief Information & Technology Architect and Executive Vice President of Verizon Communications Inc. and Verizon Nederland B.V. from January 2015 to July 21, 2017. Mr. Gurnani was responsible for developing and guiding Verizon’s technology strategy and investments. His role includes network and technology planning, development of architecture and roadmaps, continued evolution of digital platforms and oversight and direction for the Chief ... Information Officer and Chief Technology Officer teams across Verizon. Mr. Gurnani served as Chief Information Officer of Verizon Communications Inc. Mr. Gurnani has extensive experience with information technology and the telecommunications industry. He served as Senior Vice President of Product Development at Cellco Partnership, Inc. (alternate name Verizon Wireless Inc.) since April 2009 and was responsible for the innovation, development and commercialization of consumer and business products. Mr. Gurnani served as the President of the West area at Verizon Wireless from 2005 to 2008, where he was responsible for the operations throughout the western United States. He served as the Founding Officer of Verizon Wireless. He served as Vice President of Information Systems and Chief Information Officer of Cellco Partnership from April 2000 to 2008. Until 2005, he served as Vice President of Cellco and oversaw the integration of the domestic wireless operations at Bell Atlantic, Vodafone AirTouch and GTE. He served as Vice President and Chief Information Officer of Bell Atlantic Mobile from April 1997 to April 2000. Prior to joining Bell Atlantic Mobile, he served as an Executive Director of Broadband Systems at Bell Atlantic from October 1994 to April 1997. Prior to that, he served a number of information technology positions at WilTel (now WorldCom). He worked in the transportation and manufacturing industries. In 1996, he received WilTel's Chairman's recognition award for the implementation of the world's first ATM-based Switched Digital Video network in Dover Township, New Jersey. Mr. Gurnani holds a Bachelor's Degree in Industrial Engineering and a Master's in Systems Engineering from Auburn University.Read Full Background




